                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-11T18:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received March 14, 5.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of February 21st, 4 p.m.<note n="77" xml:id="d359fn77">See footnote
                        74, <ref target="#pg_424">p. 424</ref>.</note> Vice Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs advises me that his Government has entrusted to the Japanese financial
                    group the working out in the first instance in consultation with the other
                    groups of the technical details of their cooperation in China business.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
